   THE STORY OF GORBACHEV
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   Reopening a European peace offensive that was disrupted by the Armenian earthquake, Gorbachev had "extremely frank exchanges, animated, warm, passionate and solemn," said a Thatcher spokesman, requesting anonymity. Gorbachev hit the streets of London, stopping his motorcade to shake hands with about 20 people in a crowd of several hundred who cheered him outside Westminster Abbey . Soviet President Mikhail S. Gorbachev and Prime Minister Margaret Thatcher on Apr. 6, 1989 argued passionately during a four-hour meeting that covered subjects ranging from disarmament to reports of Soviet bomber sales to Libya, officials said .
